WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.839 --> 00:00:08.939
SKIPPER: Attention, this is your captain speaking.

00:00:08.939 --> 00:00:10.939
NARRATOR: You know the Penguins of Madagascar.

00:00:11.450 --> 00:00:17.210
But what you don’t know is that they’ve
been leading a double life…as secret agents.

00:00:19.800 --> 00:00:22.800
Their untold story began as four brothers…

00:00:23.320 --> 00:00:24.660
PRIVATE: Are you my family?

00:00:25.360 --> 00:00:27.420
KOWALSKI: You don’t have a family and we’re
all going to die.

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:29.820
PRIVATE: What?
SKIPPER: What’s the matter with you, Kowalski?

00:00:30.340 --> 00:00:35.740
NARRATOR: …who grew up to become masters
of disguise, espionage, and aerial assault.

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:39.380
SKIPPER: Follow me, boys! We’re going in
hot.

00:00:41.720 --> 00:00:43.720
No one likes a show-off, Private.

00:00:43.720 --> 00:00:45.960
NARRATOR: Now, when it comes to stopping a madman--

00:00:46.100 --> 00:00:48.640
DAVE: I have the power to destroy you!

00:00:48.640 --> 00:00:51.020
NARRATOR: --they’ll have some competition.

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:52.840
SKIPPER: What the heck is going on?

00:00:53.320 --> 00:00:56.460
CLASSIFIED: Remain calm, Penguins. You are
now under the protection of the North Wind.

00:00:57.140 --> 00:00:58.360
SKIPPER: We don’t even know who the heck
you are!

00:00:58.680 --> 00:01:01.340
CLASSIFIED: The North Wind is an elite undercover
interspe—

00:01:01.350 --> 00:01:04.820
SKIPPER: [Crunches loudly]
CLASSIFIED: The North Wind is an elite underco—

00:01:04.960 --> 00:01:07.520
SKIPPER: [Crunches loudly]
CLASSIFIED: —task force—

00:01:07.660 --> 00:01:09.100
SKIPPER: [Crunches loudly]
CLASSIFIED: --dedicated to he—

00:01:09.100 --> 00:01:09.980
SKIPPER: [Crunches loudly]
CLASSIFIED: [Quickly] --dedicated to helping

00:01:09.990 --> 00:01:10.610
animals who can’t—
SKIPPER: [Crunches loudly]

00:01:10.740 --> 00:01:11.240
CLASSIFIED: —help—
SKIPPER: [Crunches loudly]

00:01:11.400 --> 00:01:11.900
CLASSIFIED: —themselves.
SKIPPER: [Crunches more loudly than ever]

00:01:14.060 --> 00:01:14.640
CLASSIFIED: [Groans]

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:16.140
NARRATOR: This November…

00:01:16.520 --> 00:01:18.140
SKIPPER: We got a soggy madman to stop.

00:01:18.140 --> 00:01:19.709
CLASSIFIED: I give the orders around here.

00:01:19.709 --> 00:01:21.249
You were supposed to handcuff them!

00:01:21.249 --> 00:01:23.480
SHORTFUSE: But they don’t have hands! They just have flippers!

00:01:23.480 --> 00:01:26.240
And—And I have flippers!
So it’s flippin’ useless!

00:01:27.039 --> 00:01:29.439
NARRATOR: When the world needs saving—
DAVE: After them!

00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:33.459
SKIPPER: All right, boys. It’s just like
Cuba, Venice, Rio De Janeiro, Dusseldorf!

00:01:34.280 --> 00:01:36.700
KOWALSKI: We’ve arrived in the center of
Dublin, Ireland.

00:01:37.420 --> 00:01:41.000
SKIPPER: We gotta blend in. Riverdance!
[Riverdance music plays]

00:01:43.180 --> 00:01:44.159
NARRATOR: Heroes…

00:01:44.580 --> 00:01:45.740
KOWALSKI: We don’t need these guys.

00:01:46.060 --> 00:01:47.040
NARRATOR: …become legends.

00:01:47.220 --> 00:01:48.820
SKIPPER: Penguins are our flesh and feather!

00:01:48.959 --> 00:01:52.559
If anyone’s gonna save us…it’s us.

00:01:52.559 --> 00:01:53.959
NARRATOR: From the creators of Madagascar…

00:01:54.440 --> 00:01:56.280
CORPORAL: He hacked into our system!

00:01:56.280 --> 00:01:56.959
SKIPPER: Debbie!

00:01:56.959 --> 00:01:58.649
KOWALSKI: Dave.
SKIPPER: Dave!

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:00.680
EVA: Where’s the sound?

00:02:00.800 --> 00:02:02.580
KOWALSKI: Dave, your microphone, it’s not on!

00:02:02.580 --> 00:02:04.620
CLASSIFIED: Click on the button with the picture of the microphone.

00:02:04.620 --> 00:02:06.560
SHORTFUSE: Every time a villain calls in, this happens.

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:08.100
DAVE: Hello? Hello?

00:02:08.100 --> 00:02:10.280
KOWALSKI: Well, now we can hear you, but every—we cannot see.

00:02:10.280 --> 00:02:11.040
SHORTFUSE: Every time.

00:02:11.040 --> 00:02:12.180
CLASSIFIED: [groans] Oh, it’s like talking
to my parents.

00:02:12.180 --> 00:02:14.960
NARRATOR: Dreamworks’ Penguins of Madagascar.

00:02:14.960 --> 00:02:19.120
SKIPPER: We need to find intel on Dave’s location! All right, you, where’s Dave? Give us the goods!

00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:22.740
KOWALSKI: Sir, that’s a baby squid.
[Squid crying]

00:02:25.840 --> 00:02:26.340
SKIPPER: Sorry, laddie.

